  "description": "Trefoil knot as a lead voice: the asymmetric three-strand ring with Strand 4 floating free creates a pitch identity that is almost-but-not-quite a simple tone. At braidDepth=0.78, the coupling is deep enough that the topology is the foreground — note attacks are clean (short decay, fast response) but the sustain has a slow topological shimmer. macroKnot=0.4 pulls toward Figure-Eight's four-way interference, brightening the upper partials on held notes. strandTune=5.0 (just over a major third) gives the four strands a chordal spread that the Trefoil knot then weaves into a single melodic voice.",
